China ’s growth still needs to be led
by investment although there is room to boost consumption,
Justin Lin, the  World Bank ’s chief economist, said in Beijing.  China needs to upgrade its industries and technology and
improve productivity so investment is still important for the
country, he said at a forum in Beijing.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
